<?xml version="1.0"?>
<Fleet xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <Name>TF Redwood</Name>
  <Version>3</Version>
  <TotalPoints>3000</TotalPoints>
  <FactionKey>Stock/Alliance</FactionKey>
  <Description>Difficulty: &lt;color=yellow&gt;MODERATE&lt;/color&gt;

Task Force Redwood is a long range combined arms fleet, with success resting on the coordination of its railguns to suppress foes from a distance and protect its frontline elements. The heavy cruiser can move in and acquire target locks at medium range, protected from missiles by its advanced Tanto wing. Meanwhile the destroyers should find a good sightline safely in the rear where they can engage any locked targets. Railguns can cripple a target's offensive output and tie down their damage control teams, affording friendlies a much safer and easier engagement. It is advised to prioritize armored enemies with the railguns for maximum effect, and to keep the cruiser's bow pointed towards the enemy for maximum survivability.
  </Description>
  <SortOverrideOrder>4</SortOverrideOrder>
